      "side": 1,
      "message": "PTAL\n\nDifferences from CQD version:\n\n - Instead of sorting by (host, number, patchset), we sort just by CL ID for simplicity.\n - When building the hash, sha256 is used.\n - Only the first 8 bytes (16 hex digits) in initial patchset; I\u0027m not sure what length is good and CV computation of attempt key digest uses that length (https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/cv/internal/prjmanager/runcreator/run.go;l\u003d393?q\u003dluci%20cv%20sha256%20separator\u0026ss\u003dchromium).\n - For equivalent CL group key, an extra constant is added. I think any constant would be fine, I added \"equivalent_cl_group_key\".",
