      "writtenOn": "2021-05-17T18:17:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I know that it\u0027s not the same, but I was thinking it may be sufficient and it\u0027s simpler/shorter - the key important property is that for different runs with the same sets of patchsets the key is the same; and the chance of a collision is very small.\n\nIf the chance of collision might not be small enough, I could switch to sorting by host, number, and patchset; it\u0027s more verbose. (However, by reducing some repetition with a helper function it\u0027s alright.)",
